---
source: crates/loom/tests/cli_help.rs
expression: "loom_help(&[\"logs\"])"
---
Render (or tail) the most recent per-bead JSONL log

Usage: loom logs [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -b, --bead <ID>         Restrict the search to a specific bead id
  -w, --workspace <PATH>  Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>   Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi]
  -f, --follow            Tail the selected log: block on EOF until the file grows or the user interrupts
      --raw               Emit raw JSONL bytes verbatim (no parsing). Composes with `-f` to tail raw JSONL. Mutually exclusive with `-v` and `--path`
  -v, --verbose           Stream assistant text deltas during render — equivalent to `loom run -v`. Mutually exclusive with `--raw` and `--path`
      --path              Print the resolved log file path and exit. Mutually exclusive with `-f`, `-v`, `--raw`
  -h, --help              Print help
